    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <div class="box"> 
    <style> 
        body{ color: white;
              background-color: black; 
              font-size: 17px; }
        h1{   color: blueviolet; 
              font-size: 42px; } 
        h2{   color: red; 
              font-size: 30px; }
        .box {border: 5px solid red; /* Adds a solid red border */
              padding: 10px; /* Adds space inside the border */
              width: 200px; /* Sets width */
              height: 100px; /* Sets height */ }
     </style>
</head>
<body>
     <!-- Title of the cake -->
     <h1> Chocolate Cake </h1>

     <!-- Description of the chocolate cake -->
     <p>  This is a rich, moist chocolate cake with a deep, decadent chocolate flavor and a tender, melt-in-your-mouth texture. It's a showstopper when served, and with its perfect texture and delicious flavor, this chocolate cake is sure to satisfy any chocolate lover's dreams! 🍫🎂 </p>
 
     <!-- List of ingredients -->
     <h2> Ingredients: </h2>
     <ul>
          <li> 1 ¾ cups all-purpose flour </li>
          <li> 1 ½ teaspoons baking powder </li>
          <li> ½ teaspoon baking soda </li>
          <li> ½ teaspoon salt </li>
          <li> 1 cup unsweetened cocoa powder </li>
          <li> 1 ½ cups granulated sugar </li>
          <li> 2 large eggs </li>
          <li> 1 teaspoon vanilla extract </li>
          <li> ½ cup vegetable oil </li>
          <li> 1 cup whole milk </li>
          <li> ½ cup boiling water </li>
     </ul>
 
     <!-- Instructions for making the cake -->
     <h2> Method: </h2>
     <ol>
         <!-- Step-by-step baking instructions -->
         <li> Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). </li>
         <li> Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans or line with parchment paper. </li>
         <li> In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cocoa powder, and sugar. </li>
         <li> Add the eggs, vanilla extract, and vegetable oil to the dry ingredients. </li>
         <li> Mix until combined. </li>
         <li> Slowly add the milk while continuing to mix. The batter will be thin. </li>
         <li> Add the boiling water: Carefully stir in the boiling water. </li>
         <li> Pour the batter into the pans. </li>
         <li> Divide the batter evenly between the two prepared cake pans. </li>
         <li> Bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. </li>
         <li> Let the cakes cool in the pans for about 10 minutes, then transfer to wire racks to cool completely. </li>
     </ol>
</div>
</body>
